WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-IN

00:00:00.010 --> 00:00:01.390
Are European travellers safe?

00:00:02.970 --> 00:00:06.750
Should we cancel or continue these trips in

00:00:06.750 --> 00:00:07.250
such a war-like situation?

00:00:07.530 --> 00:00:09.690
Friends, I have been getting a lot of

00:00:09.690 --> 00:00:11.310
emails and messages from the last few days

00:00:11.310 --> 00:00:13.950
in which viewers are asking what we should

00:00:13.950 --> 00:00:15.570
do in this situation.

00:00:16.090 --> 00:00:19.050
A lot of travellers' tickets, stay, etc.

00:00:19.310 --> 00:00:20.310
are fully booked.

00:00:20.730 --> 00:00:22.490
Their plans are already in April, May or

00:00:22.490 --> 00:00:25.490
June and they are confused about what to

00:00:25.490 --> 00:00:25.990
do.

00:00:26.110 --> 00:00:29.990
So, today's video is about how to deal

00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:32.230
with this situation and what changes we need

00:00:32.230 --> 00:00:33.670
to bring in European planning so that you

00:00:33.670 --> 00:00:34.830
don't have to worry if such a geopolitical

00:00:34.830 --> 00:00:36.010
situation arises.

00:00:38.130 --> 00:00:40.470
I am Heena Shah and I make videos

00:00:40.470 --> 00:00:42.170
related to Europe budget travel and tips.

00:00:42.830 --> 00:00:44.470
Do watch all my videos for a lovely

00:00:44.470 --> 00:00:45.250
trip to Europe.

00:00:45.470 --> 00:00:47.110
First of all, it is important to understand

00:00:47.110 --> 00:00:50.390
that in such a geopolitical situation, European tourism

00:00:50.390 --> 00:00:52.530
and destinations are not directly affected.

00:00:52.530 --> 00:00:54.230
The only thing that is affected is flights

00:00:54.230 --> 00:00:54.890
and routes.

00:00:55.170 --> 00:00:59.810
So, your flights may get cancelled, delayed or

00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:02.650
you may have to take longer routes due

00:01:02.650 --> 00:01:04.870
to closure of airspaces, etc.

00:01:05.310 --> 00:01:08.510
So, a smart move should be to book

00:01:08.510 --> 00:01:09.810
always refundable flights.

00:01:10.850 --> 00:01:14.790
I understand that cheap flights are non-refundable.

00:01:15.390 --> 00:01:18.850
So, it is better to book refundable flights

00:01:18.850 --> 00:01:21.950
by paying a little more.
Next thing is that you should always pay

00:01:21.950 --> 00:01:26.570
attention to the travel advisories of the airlines.

00:01:26.810 --> 00:01:28.970
Do not rely on any news from WhatsApp

00:01:28.970 --> 00:01:30.550
or any other channel.

00:01:32.890 --> 00:01:34.430
Most important, do not panic.

00:01:34.850 --> 00:01:38.930
If you panic, you won't be able to

00:01:38.930 --> 00:01:40.450
think straight and you won't be able to

00:01:40.450 --> 00:01:41.930
make a right decision for yourself.

00:01:41.930 --> 00:01:45.630
So, be calm and understand that whatever travel

00:01:45.630 --> 00:01:47.590
advisories are being given by your country or

00:01:47.590 --> 00:01:50.590
destination country, you should follow them.

00:01:50.610 --> 00:01:55.530
So, follow the official advisories and stay updated

00:01:55.530 --> 00:01:56.030
with the information you get from your airlines.

00:01:56.090 --> 00:01:57.950
Do not immediately cancel your plans.

00:01:58.070 --> 00:01:59.110
That's not the right thing to do.

00:01:59.310 --> 00:02:02.110
We panic and think that I don't think

00:02:02.110 --> 00:02:03.110
I can travel right now.

00:02:03.350 --> 00:02:04.750
So, I will just cancel my plans.

00:02:05.010 --> 00:02:05.630
Do not do that.

00:02:05.630 --> 00:02:08.630
Because these airlines or wherever you have booked

00:02:08.630 --> 00:02:10.510
your trips from, they might give you a

00:02:10.510 --> 00:02:12.230
credit, they might give you a different date

00:02:12.230 --> 00:02:13.190
to travel on.

00:02:13.390 --> 00:02:14.850
They will give you some option or the

00:02:14.850 --> 00:02:16.330
other before you cancel the flight.

00:02:16.670 --> 00:02:18.910
Think, listen to all the options and then

00:02:18.910 --> 00:02:19.770
take your decision.

00:02:20.310 --> 00:02:23.870
Next, whenever you book a stay, you should

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:26.430
always book refundable bookings.

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:28.370
Because that's what I do. 

00:02:29.230 --> 00:02:32.550
I have always booked refundable bookings on all

00:02:32.550 --> 00:02:35.230
our trips.
In case something or the other changes, I

00:02:35.230 --> 00:02:37.910
can always get the booking cancelled and get

00:02:37.910 --> 00:02:38.670
the money back.

00:02:38.930 --> 00:02:40.850
So, that is very very important, especially in

00:02:40.850 --> 00:02:41.990
these kinds of situations.

00:02:42.090 --> 00:02:43.810
Thirdly, you have to take care of one

00:02:43.810 --> 00:02:44.330
more thing.

00:02:44.730 --> 00:02:47.350
That whatever itinerary you have to make, you

00:02:47.350 --> 00:02:48.010
don't have to make it a back-to

00:02:48.010 --> 00:02:48.910
-back packed itinerary.

00:02:49.710 --> 00:02:51.150
You have to keep a buffer in between.

00:02:51.510 --> 00:02:52.830
So, it's not like you land at one

00:02:52.830 --> 00:02:56.270
place and then immediately go to another place

00:02:56.270 --> 00:02:57.350
the next day.
And then you know next.

00:02:57.530 --> 00:02:58.870
If you have made such a back-to

00:02:58.870 --> 00:03:01.530
-back itinerary jam-pack, then it can be

00:03:01.530 --> 00:03:01.910
a problem.

00:03:01.910 --> 00:03:04.650
Because in case there are flight delays or

00:03:04.650 --> 00:03:08.010
you reach late due to longer routes, then

00:03:08.010 --> 00:03:10.610
you won't have the buffer time to adjust

00:03:10.610 --> 00:03:11.110
this delay.

00:03:11.470 --> 00:03:14.250
So, always keep your plans fluid.

00:03:14.650 --> 00:03:16.550
Again, I have said this earlier also and

00:03:16.550 --> 00:03:17.330
again I am insisting.

00:03:17.610 --> 00:03:18.890
Don't make time-stamped itineraries.

00:03:19.950 --> 00:03:21.850
Because you never know when there can be

00:03:21.850 --> 00:03:22.630
a change in the plans.

00:03:23.470 --> 00:03:25.310
So, keeping a buffer time is very very

00:03:25.310 --> 00:03:26.050
important.

00:03:26.650 --> 00:03:28.850
Next, don't ignore travel insurance at all.

00:03:29.870 --> 00:03:31.770
As a mandatory requirement, we always take travel

00:03:31.770 --> 00:03:32.270
insurance.

00:03:32.710 --> 00:03:33.510
But we don't read the fine print.

00:03:34.790 --> 00:03:36.170
A lot of times, a lot of such

00:03:36.170 --> 00:03:37.510
things are not covered in travel insurance.

00:03:38.570 --> 00:03:40.210
So, whenever you take a travel insurance policy,

00:03:40.550 --> 00:03:41.710
please read what is covered in case of

00:03:41.710 --> 00:03:44.690
flight delay cancellation or various other war-like

00:03:44.690 --> 00:03:45.690
situations.

00:03:47.130 --> 00:03:48.050
And what is not covered.

00:03:48.330 --> 00:03:49.950
So, pay attention to the fine print in

00:03:49.950 --> 00:03:50.630
the travel insurance.

00:03:50.790 --> 00:03:52.570
And take this type of insurance so that

00:03:52.570 --> 00:03:53.730
you can get good coverage.

00:03:54.690 --> 00:03:56.930
And yes, if a lot of travellers have

00:03:56.930 --> 00:03:59.430
already booked and now this is a situation

00:03:59.430 --> 00:04:01.250
that has arrived, then what can you do?

00:04:01.710 --> 00:04:03.950
Again, repeating, don't panic.

00:04:04.490 --> 00:04:07.050
Follow the official updates from the airlines.

00:04:08.310 --> 00:04:10.310
Don't read the messages from the social media

00:04:10.310 --> 00:04:12.750
and cancel your plans.

00:04:14.490 --> 00:04:16.290
And one very very important thing.

00:04:16.630 --> 00:04:19.709
If there is no issue in your destination,

00:04:19.769 --> 00:04:22.150
then frankly speaking, you don't need to cancel

00:04:22.150 --> 00:04:22.650
your plans.

00:04:22.850 --> 00:04:24.610
You just need to adjust your mode of

00:04:24.610 --> 00:04:28.390
travel or bring some changes in it.

00:04:28.830 --> 00:04:31.530
If the destination is completely peaceful, normal travel

00:04:31.530 --> 00:04:34.410
is going on, everything is under control, then

00:04:34.410 --> 00:04:36.770
definitely you can go visit these countries.

00:04:37.070 --> 00:04:38.650
You do not need to directly cancel your

00:04:38.650 --> 00:04:39.190
plans.

00:04:39.510 --> 00:04:40.910
So, I hope in this video, I have

00:04:40.910 --> 00:04:43.170
answered a few of your queries considering the

00:04:43.170 --> 00:04:45.630
situation that arises every now and then, especially

00:04:45.630 --> 00:04:47.950
the geopolitical situations like the one which is

00:04:47.950 --> 00:04:48.710
going on currently.

00:04:49.270 --> 00:04:50.310
And yes friends, I would like to share

00:04:50.310 --> 00:04:51.430
one thing with you.

00:04:51.430 --> 00:04:53.610
Based on my experience, which I have been

00:04:53.610 --> 00:04:56.770
travelling for so many years, the travel plans

00:04:56.770 --> 00:04:57.770
are never predictable.

00:04:58.430 --> 00:05:01.090
There can be some changes which can be

00:05:01.090 --> 00:05:02.070
completely unpredictable.

00:05:02.450 --> 00:05:04.810
Sometimes the weather changes, sometimes there is some

00:05:04.810 --> 00:05:06.750
issue with the airlines, and sometimes some other

00:05:06.750 --> 00:05:07.250
issue.

00:05:07.250 --> 00:05:08.770
So for this, you have to always be

00:05:08.770 --> 00:05:13.450
ready, mentally prepared that any change can happen

00:05:13.450 --> 00:05:13.930
at any time.

00:05:13.930 --> 00:05:15.390
But this does not mean that you cancel

00:05:15.390 --> 00:05:16.110
your plans.

00:05:16.810 --> 00:05:19.650
It means that you think wisely and take

00:05:19.650 --> 00:05:20.610
practical decisions.

00:05:21.250 --> 00:05:23.710
If you have more queries, then please write

00:05:23.710 --> 00:05:24.890
to me in the comment section.

00:05:25.230 --> 00:05:26.810
I will try and answer all your queries.

00:05:27.170 --> 00:05:29.650
And keep following my videos for more such

00:05:29.650 --> 00:05:30.550
practical updates.

00:05:30.890 --> 00:05:31.390
Thank you. (Transcribed by TurboScribe. ai)

